Here’s a basic example:

```cpp
// Connect button's clicked signal to a custom slot
connect(button, &QPushButton::clicked, this, &MyClass::onButtonClicked);

void MyClass::onButtonClicked() {
    // Code to execute when button is clicked
    qDebug() << "Button clicked!";
}
```
This connects the button’s 'clicked' signal to the 'onButtonClicked' slot. When the button is clicked, the slot function runs. Let me know if you'd like to explore more about signals and slots or other Qt features.
